{{Infobox football biography |name = Thomas Boden |image = |caption = |fullname = Thomas Henry Boden |birth_date = June 1860 |birth_place = Wrexham, Wales |death_date = <!--{{death date and age|1927|||1860|||df=yes}}--> |death_place = Shropshire |height = |position = RW |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 1879–1880 |clubs1 = [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = |clubs2 = |caps2 = |goals2 = |totalcaps = |totalgoals = |nationalyears1 = 1880 |nationalteam1 = [[Wales national football team|Wales]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''Thomas Boden ''' (born June 1860) was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] [[association football|footballer]]. He was part of the [[Wales national football team]], playing 1 match on 15 March 1880 against England.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=2147|title=Wales player database 1872 to 2013|publisher=eu-football.info|accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref>
At club level, he played for [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] from 1879–1880.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/thomas-boden_2/ |title=Thomas Boden |publisher=worldfootball.net |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> He played as a right wing in the [[1879 Welsh Cup Final]], where his team lost against [[Newtown A.F.C.|Newtown White Star]] with 1-0.
