{{short description|Italian metallurgist and alchemist}} {{Infobox person | name = Tommaso Masini | image = Via di peretola 43, targa tommaso masini,.JPG | birth_name = Tommaso di Giovanni Masini | birth_date = 1462 | birth_place = [[Peretola]] | death_date = 1520 (aged 58) | death_cause = [[Cholera]] | death_place = [[Rome, Italy]] | burial_place = [[Church of Sant'Agata dei Goti]] }}
'''Tommaso di Giovanni Masini''' ({{circa|1462}} – 1520), known as '''Zoroaster Da Peretola''', was a friend and collaborator of [[Leonardo Da Vinci]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/leonardo-da-vinci_%28Dizionario-Biografico%29/ |title=Leonardo da Vinci |dictionary=[[Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani]] |volume=64 |year=2005 |access-date=4 June 2014 |language=it |first=Pietro |last=Marani |publisher=[[Treccani]]}}</ref><ref name=Nicholl>{{cite book |last=Nicholl |first=Charles |author-link=Charles Nicholl (author) |title=Leonardo Da Vinci: The Flights of the Mind |title-link=Leonardo da Vinci: The Flights of the Mind |publisher=[[Penguin (publisher)|Penguin]] |year=2005 |isbn=9780141944241 |oclc=56334378}}</ref>
According to [[Scipione Ammirato]], he was born in [[Peretola]], near [[Florence]], and he was the child of a [[gardener]],<ref>{{cite book |first=Scipione |last=Ammirato |author-link=Scipione Ammirato |title=Opuscoli |volume=II |year=1637 |page=242 |oclc=46690828 |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=xhYY-El9ZMMC&pg=PA242}}</ref> althoug he said he was the [[Illegitimate child]] of [[Bernardo Rucellai]], [[Lorenzo il Magnifico]] [[brother-in-law]].<ref name=Nicholl/><ref>{{cite news |last=Conti |first=Marco |title=Tommaso Masini, detto Zoroastro |url=http://wwwext.comune.fi.it/comune/organi/q5/gen04/11.pdf |language=it |publisher=Comune di Firenze |year=2004 |access-date=10 October 2018 |format=PDF}}</ref>
In 1505 he returned to Florence and worked with Leonardo in ''[[The Battle of Anghiari (painting)|The Battle of Anghiari]]''.<ref>{{cite book |last=Laurenza |first=Domenico |title=Leonardo: On Flight |publisher=Giunti Editore |year=2004 |isbn=9788809037847 |pages=119 |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=ZeExGUY_vKQC&printsec=frontcover}}</ref> He proved the [[ornithopter]] and flew 1.000 meters before landing abruptly.<ref>{{cite book |first=Leonardo |last=da Vinci |author-link=Leonardo da Vinci |title=Codex on the Flight of Birds |title-link=Codex on the Flight of Birds |year=1505 |publisher=[[Biblioteca Reale]] |location=Turin}}</ref>
He was buried at the [[Church of Sant'Agata dei Goti]].<ref name=Nicholl/>
